column1: Number of Rhode Island Residents Who Have Completed Primary Vaccine Series by Age Group and Week
Source: Rhode Island Department of Health (RIDOH); Rhode Island Child and Adult Immunization Registry (RICAIR)

NOTES: Congregate setting residents are included. Out-of-state residents are excluded. 
Data reflect Rhode Island residents who have completed all recommended doses of a primary vaccine series, which includes the single-dose Johnson and Johnson vaccine. Small numbers are shown as <5 in line with RIDOH's Small Numbers Policy. We provide weekly data to help show broader trends over time. Fluctuations in these data may be due to a variety of factors, such as vaccine availability and eligibility criteria. Please use caution when interpreting these data.
